The '''Japanese submarine ''I-28''''' was one of 20 [[Type B submarine|Type B]] [[cruiser submarine]]s of the B1 [[ship class|sub-class]] built for the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] (IJN) during the 1940s.
==Design and description== The Type B submarines were derived from the earlier KD6 sub-class of the {{Sclass-|Kaidai|submarine|4}} and were equipped with an aircraft to enhance their scouting ability. They [[Displacement (ship)|displaced]] {{Convert|2589|LT|t|0|disp=flip}} surfaced and {{Convert|3654|LT|t|0|disp=flip}} submerged. The submarines were {{convert|108.7|m|ftin|sp=us}} long, had a [[beam (nautical)|beam]] of {{convert|9.3|m|ftin|sp=us}} and a [[draft (hull)|draft]] of {{convert|5.1|m|ftin|sp=us}}. They had a diving depth of {{convert|100|m|ft|sp=us}}.<ref name=b4>Bagnasco, p. 189</ref>
For surface running, the boats were powered by two {{convert|6200|bhp|lk=in|0|adj=on}} [[diesel engine]]s, each driving one [[propeller shaft]]. When submerged each propeller was driven by a {{convert|1000|hp|0|adj=on}} [[electric motor]]. They could reach {{convert|23.6|kn|lk=in}} on the surface and {{convert|8|kn}} underwater.<ref name=c5>Chesneau, p. 200</ref> On the surface, the ''B1''s had a range of {{convert|14000|nmi|lk=in}} at {{convert|16|kn}}; submerged, they had a range of {{convert|96|nmi|abbr=on}} at {{convert|3|kn}}.<ref name=cd3/>
The boats were armed with six internal bow {{convert|53.3|cm|in|1|abbr=on|sp=us}} [[torpedo tube]]s and carried a total of 17 [[torpedo]]es. They were also armed with a single [[14 cm/40 11th Year Type naval gun|{{convert|140|mm|in|abbr=on}}/40]] [[deck gun]] and two single mounts for [[Type 96 25 mm AT/AA Gun|{{convert|25|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} Type 96]] [[anti-aircraft gun]]s.<ref name=cd3>Carpenter & Dorr, p. 102</ref> In the Type Bs, the aircraft [[hangar]] was faired into the base of the [[conning tower]]. A single [[Aircraft catapult|catapult]] was positioned on the forward deck.<ref name=cd3/>
==Construction and career== ''I-28'' was commissioned at [[Kobe, Japan]] on February 6, 1942. The submarine participated in the [[Battle of the Coral Sea]] in May 1942. Returning to base at [[Chuuk Lagoon|Truk]] in the central Pacific, ''I-28'' was torpedoed and sunk with all hands (88 officers and men) by the [[United States Navy]] submarine {{USS|Tautog|SS-199|2}} at {{coord|06|30|N|152|00|E|display=title, inline}} on 17 May 1942.
